            <title>[FLUME-784] MemoryChannel should poll with timeout on take() rather than block indefinitely</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-784</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MemoryChannel is currently completely blocking; it uses ArrayBlockingQueue#put() and #take() rather than offer() and poll(). This is suboptimal for certain runner strategies and background tasks. For now, MemoryChannel should use #poll&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/error.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; where x is some reasonable (ideally configurable) timeout.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
